In the chapter, the formula for the net capital spending is given as:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net capital spending}&=\text{Net fixed assets at the end}\\
&-\text{Net fixed assets at the beginning}\\
&+\text{Depreciation}
\end{aligned}$$

Moreover, we know that the net fixed asset is given using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net fixed asset}&=\text{Gross fixed assets}-\text{Accumulated depreciation}
\end{aligned}$$

**Accumulated depreciation** is the cumulative depreciation of a certain asset up to a certain timeframe in its lifespan.

In this case, we know that the accumulated depreciation (AD) will cancel each other out based on the description provided in Step 4, we will then get:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{NFA}_{\text{end}}-\text{NFA}_{\text{beginning}}+\text{Depreciation}&=\text{FA}_{\text{end}}-\text{FA}_{\text{beginning}}
\end{aligned}$$
